    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        Ten Years After the Flint Water Crisis, Distrust and Anger Linger
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/anna-clark">Anna Clark</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>, Photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-04EDT05:00">May 4, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

        <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
        <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" >            A city is forever changed, and so is residents’ relationship with their water. The betrayal of trust by the institutions meant to protect Flint’s residents has made some of them extra cautious as they look to keep themselves and their community safe.
        </h2>
    </div>
    
</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left      article-meta-1--hide-byline " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/anna-clark">Anna Clark</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>, Photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-04EDT05:00">May 4, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
    </time>

