<figure
    data-pp-id="33"
    data-pp-blocktype="embed"
    class="bb-embed size08 center  wide-sm wrap
                hide-print
        ">

    


                        <p class="heading-quote"><strong>Teagan Medlin was a teenager in Flint</strong> during the water crisis. Now, the 25-year-old is the mother of three, including a newborn named Audrina. She lives at a recovery house for people with substance use disorder. As she works through her own recovery, she also struggles with whether it’s OK to expose her children to the water.</p>
            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
    
    
    
    </figcaption>


</figure>

        
    
                    

